38#include "kdc_locl.h"
39
40void
41kdc_openlog(krb5_context context,
42 const char *service,
43 krb5_kdc_configuration *config)
44{
45 char **s = NULL, **p;
46 krb5_initlog(context, "kdc", &config->logf);
47 s = krb5_config_get_strings(context, NULL, service, "logging", NULL);
48 if(s == NULL)
49 s = krb5_config_get_strings(context, NULL, "logging", service, NULL);
50 if(s){
51 for(p = s; *p; p++)
52 krb5_addlog_dest(context, config->logf, *p);
53 krb5_config_free_strings(s);
54 }else {
55 char *ss;
56 if (asprintf(&ss, "0-1/FILE:%s/%s", hdb_db_dir(context),
57 KDC_LOG_FILE) < 0)
58 err(1, "out of memory");
59 krb5_addlog_dest(context, config->logf, ss);
60 free(ss);
61 }
62 krb5_set_warn_dest(context, config->logf);
63}
64
65char*
66kdc_log_msg_va(krb5_context context,
67 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
68 int level, const char *fmt, va_list ap)
69{
70 char *msg;
71 krb5_vlog_msg(context, config->logf, &msg, level, fmt, ap);
72 return msg;
73}
74
75char*
76kdc_log_msg(krb5_context context,
77 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
78 int level, const char *fmt, ...)
79{
80 va_list ap;
81 char *s;
82 va_start(ap, fmt);
83 s = kdc_log_msg_va(context, config, level, fmt, ap);
84 va_end(ap);
85 return s;
86}
87
88void
89kdc_log(krb5_context context,
90 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
91 int level, const char *fmt, ...)
92{
93 va_list ap;
94 char *s;
95 va_start(ap, fmt);
96 s = kdc_log_msg_va(context, config, level, fmt, ap);
97 if(s) free(s);
98 va_end(ap);
99}
